{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 15:08:55.209571", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission recorded.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"router_dist_1_1\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"ospf_area_misconfiguration\"]\n\nRecommended next steps (operational):\n- Reconfigure router_dist_1_1 OSPF network statements to use the correct area (match core area, e.g., area 0 or the area's ID used by the rest of the network).\n- After config change, verify OSPF adjacency with core routers and confirm routes for 10.200.0.0/24 appear in router_dist_1_1 routing table.\n- Confirm DHCP reachability from router_dist_1_1 (ping 10.200.0.8) and then from hosts on 10.1.1.0/24 obtain DHCP leases.\n- Validate end-to-end connectivity and monitor for any residual issues.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2340, "output_tokens": 185, "total_tokens": 2525, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
